node.text: One week ago, on June 27th, I hosted some of my nearest and dearest friends at the Polo Lounge Private Salon in the Beverly Hills Hotel for an intimate sit down dinner to celebrate my birthday and the television premiere of "Pass The Mic: BET Awards Edition." I had no idea I'd end up passing the mic to every artist in the room, transforming the intimate affair into an impromptu "Pass The Mic" live jam session. As I often say, I feel fortunate to call many of my musical heroes my friends. In fact, it is that sentiment that inspired "Pass The Mic" and remains at the foundation of the show. I felt such joy sharing these incredibly special moments with so many of my loved ones, most of whom I hadn't seen in a year and a half. It was truly a magical night. Here's a little taste of the magic featuring Philip Bailey, Verdine White, and El Debarge. As El was finishing a rendition of "All This Love" and "I Like It," I asked him if he could play any Earth Wind & Fire songs. He replied, "I can play them all." I passed the mic to Philip and the bass to Verdine, and the magic multiplied. This moment brought me to tears, as it was this song that set off the very first edition of "Pass The Mic," one year ago, almost to the day. The serendipity was chilling.
